The county assembly of Samburu on Monday passed the Constitution Amendment Bill, 2020. This brings to 12, the counties which have passed the Bill. Other counties that have passed the Bill are Nairobi, Vihiga, Laikipia, Kisii, Siaya, Kisumu, Kajiado, West Pokot, Busia, Trans Nzoia and Homa Bay. So far, only Baringo County has rejected the Bill. Twenty-four out of 47 counties are required to pass the Bill. More to follow...